radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled with small amount of surrounding fluid and fat stranding, most consistent with acute appendicitis. No evidence of extraluminal gas or drainable fluid collection. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, uterus, and ovaries appear normal. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No abnormal vascular findings.
